# Git: commit and push when work is done

When you finish a job that changed this repo:

1. Run `git status`. Stage only intentional changes (avoid unrelated paths such as `.claude/worktrees`, local env files, or accidental edits unless the user asked to include them).
2. Commit with a clear message describing what changed and why.
3. Push to `origin` on the current branch (`git push origin HEAD` or `git push origin main` as appropriate).

Do not skip push solely because you assume the user prefers local-only work—they asked for pushes after tasks.

If push fails (auth, conflicts), fix what you can (e.g. pull --rebase with permission), report clearly if blocked.
